The paper proposes a new graphical representation for utility functions and demonstrates its value in decision making. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, as these fields often deal with decision making and optimization problems. The paper also mentions the efficiency of computation, which suggests that it may belong to the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses an interactive elicitation procedure, which may indicate that it belongs to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-categories, as these fields often deal with decision making in complex systems.
